# Core Feature Integration Plan

Now that Aura AI is deployed, we will transition it from a mock-based prototype to a functional trading platform by integrating the AI engine and a persistent database.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend: Database Layer
- Implement `backend/database.py` to handle SQLAlchemy engine and sessions.
- Un-comment and refine models in [backend/models/schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/models/schemas.py).
- Integrate DB dependency into routes.

### AI Engine: Signals Integration
- Update [backend/main.py](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/main.py) to include a `/api/ai/predict/{symbol}` endpoint.
- Connect the frontend "AI Signals" page to this endpoint.

### Trading Bot: Live Control
- Integrate [TradingCoordinator](file:///c:/Users/User/AI/backend/services/trading_coordinator.py#7-58) into the FastAPI app state.
- Create endpoints to toggle auto-trading and view status.

### Frontend: Production Readiness
- Replace hardcoded `http://localhost:8000` with an environment variable `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `pytest` on the `ai_engine` to ensure predictions still work with real data.
- Add integration tests for the new API endpoints.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the "AI Signals" page and verify it displays predictions based on live market data.
2. Toggle the "Start Live Trading" button and verify the status update.
